The Beckhoff CCAT FPGA linux driver provides support for different CCAT functions:
==================================================================================
- Ethernet
- GPIO
- SRAM
- FPGA update

Supported devices:
- CX50xx
- CX51xx
- CX20xx


How to build and install the kernel modules:
============================================
Install 'ccat'
1. cd into ccat <src_dir>
2. make && make install


How to configure the driver:
============================
All functions are implemented in a single kernel module. To disable some of the functions modify 'static const struct ccat_driver *const drivers[]' in 'module.c' according to your needs.
